1. Tableau is used for fast interactive data visualization.


2. Tableau versions are Desktop, Server, Online, Public.


3. Dataset connects using the Connect option.


4. Connect pane shows data sources.


5. Data source page is for preview and manage data.


6. Joins combine related tables.


7. Dashboard, worksheet, story are for organizing analysis.


8. Categorical/Numerical columns define data field type.


9. Dimensions are qualitative, Measures are quantitative.


10. Charts represent data patterns.


11. “Show me” suggests chart types.


12. Data pane lists all fields.


13. Analytics pane provides analysis tools.


14. Marks card customizes visual marks.


15. Color, text, tooltip, size, detail control appearance.


16. Filters refine displayed data.


17. Column/Row shelves arrange fields.


18. Alias, hierarchy, calculated field customize fields.


19. Aggregate functions summarize data.


20. Text and logical functions perform conditions.


21. Maps show geographical data.


22. Map types are symbol, filled, density.


23. Pie chart in map via Pie marks.


24. Map layer added from map options.


25. Clusters group similar data.


26. Forecasting uses Forecast option.


27. Trendline added from Analytics pane.


28. Dashboard size set in options.


29. Table calculation computes derived values.


30. Examples: Rank, Running total, Percent.


31. Data visualization means graphical data representation.
32.
